==Introduction==
The '''Text Property Type''' represents a multi-line textual content.

The Wiki Automation Tool supports editing, viewing and searching on the Text properties.


==Definition==

The Text Property extends a common definition of the [[Help:Property|Property Definition]] with the following elements:

<pre>
<property ... size={SIZE} rows={ROWS}>
</property>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {SIZE}
| A length of the input field. Default value: 50.
|-
! {ROWS}
| A number of initially displayed rows. Default value: 2.
|}


==Semantic database==
The Text Property is implemented as a [[Special:Types/Text]] MediaWiki datatype.


==Example==
<pre>
<property name="Objective" type="Text" label="Objective" attribute="objective" rows="5" size="80">
  <description>A free text format to describe the objective of a certain entity.</description>
  <instruction>A "Objective" is a text value that reflects an explanation of an objective for a taxonomy element. </instruction>
</property>
</pre>


==User Interface==
* '''View Page'''
The property displays a text value entered by the user.

* '''Edit Page'''
The property provides multi-line text input field.
A length of the input field is controlled by the 'size' attribute.
A number of initially displayed rows is controlled by the "rows" attribute.

* '''Search Page'''
The property allows user to choose a search operator from the following options: ''Starts with, Contains, Equals, Ends with, Has any''
and allows user to enter a desired value in multi-line text input field.
